data.name: TextBox1.Text
data.value:
Welcome to the ArduPirates Management Console, APMC for short.
I've started developing this application to replace the 'old' ArduCopter Configurator, which was based on National Instrument's LabVIEW framework. This framework is very difficult to understand and it was not helping the ArduPirates group of developers get forward with interfacing their Arduino code for quadrocopters, hexacopters and octocopters.
To be able to continue development on the hardware side of things and not be limited by the configuration software, I chose to develop this application using a fairly easy to understand programming language. Preferably by using a free development platform. I decided on Microsoft Visual Basic 2010 Express. For many of us out there, VB is something we've all been programming in, most of us for macro's in Excel and Word. The Arduino language, C, is a little more difficult to master. Although I personally am perfectly capable of programming in C, I wanted this side of the solution (the PC side) to be as accessible as possible. I hope this project will be picked up by others and I hope to see it grow into a complete solution.
The functionality I have envisioned for it includes, but is not limited to; full ground control station with live video, HUD overlay, full fledged mission planner, a complete configuration solution including full command-line access to the ArduPirates hardware, complete PID tuning, and whatever else we can think of.
This application needs the .NET framework to be installed for it in order to work. Since virtually any Windows computer has .NET installed, the install base for this application is huge. The advantage of it being that it is very small in size, especially when compared to the 'old' ArduCopter Configurator (counting with the NI LabVIEW framework). It needs no installation, just run the executable and you're on your way.
I've spend a lot of effort trying to accomplish every single function with native code or standard Windows API's. No third party components or plugins have been used. Any fresh install of Microsoft Visual Basic 2010 Express will allow this project to compile without any special additions.
The graphic components inside this application, like for instance the ADI and the transmitter calibration bars, are custom work by my hand and completely open - there are no external graphics inside this application (in the form of resources) besides the ArduPirates logo. Every other graphic is achieved programmatically (drawn with code).
I hope you enjoy using this application. I hope you see it's potential and I sure hope you are enticed to contribute to it's development in some way or another.
I very much appreciate any feedback or comments that you might have. Please contact me via email at info@kidogo.nl and drop me a line.
Best regards,
Kim Dalmeijer aka Kidogo.
